- Add "task_management applied" at the beginning of the chat message.
- Check current task context from .status/tasks
- Update progress in @status.md

## Required files and folders
  - .status/tasks: Current development tasks and requirements, source of tasks definitions
  - [status.md](mdc:.status/status.md) : Project progress and state
  
## Workflow steps
  1. READ tasks in .status/tasks folder :
     - Parse current task requirements
     - Extract acceptance criteria
     - Identify dependencies
  
  2. VALIDATE against Cursor rules defined in .cursor/rules :
     - Confirm architectural alignment
     - Check component interactions
     - Take into agent chat every useful rule files
  
  3. UPDATE [status.md](mdc:.status/status.md):
     - Mark task as in-progress
     - Track completion of sub-tasks
     - Document any blockers
     - When the task is completed, move it in section "Completed features"
     - Always make updates in english in file
  
  4. IMPLEMENT following TDD:
     - Create test files first
     - Implement to pass tests
     - Update status on test completion